# Books Library

A full-stack web application for managing personal book collections, built with FastAPI and vanilla JavaScript.

## Project Overview

This is a complete book management system that allows users to:
- Add, edit, and delete books from their collection
- Mark books as favorites
- Search and filter books by category, author, or title
- Sort books by various criteria
- View books in a responsive grid layout

## Architecture

**Backend (FastAPI)**:
- RESTful API with full CRUD operations
- SQLAlchemy ORM with SQLite database (configurable)
- Pydantic models for request/response validation
- Automatic API documentation via OpenAPI/Swagger

**Frontend (Vanilla JS)**:
- Single-page application with dynamic content loading
- Responsive design with CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Real-time search and filtering
- Modal-based editing interface
- Font Awesome icons

## Project Structure

```
/app/src/
├── main.py              # FastAPI application entry point
├── models.py            # SQLAlchemy database models
├── dtos.py             # Pydantic schemas for API validation
├── database.py         # Database configuration and session management
├── routers/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── books.py        # Book API endpoints (/books)
└── static/
    ├── index.html      # Main web interface
    ├── styles.css      # CSS styles and responsive design
    └── script.js       # Frontend JavaScript application
```

## Database Schema

### Book Model
- `id`: Primary key (auto-increment)
- `title`: Book title (indexed)
- `author`: Author name (indexed)
- `pages`: Number of pages
- `category`: Book category (default: "Fiction", indexed)
- `favorite`: Favorite status (default: false, indexed)

## API Endpoints

All endpoints are prefixed with `/books`:

- `GET /books/` - List all books
- `POST /books/` - Create a new book
- `GET /books/{book_id}` - Get specific book
- `PUT /books/{book_id}` - Update book
- `DELETE /books/{book_id}` - Delete book
- `PATCH /books/{book_id}/favorite` - Toggle favorite status

## Features

**Book Management**:
- Add books with title, author, pages, category
- Edit existing book details
- Delete books with confirmation
- Mark books as favorites

**Search & Filter**:
- Real-time text search (title/author)
- Filter by category (20+ categories available)
- Filter by favorite status
- Sort by title, author, pages, or category
- Toggle sort direction (ascending/descending)

**User Interface**:
- Responsive design (mobile-friendly)
- Grid layout for book display
- Modal dialogs for editing
- Loading states and error handling
- Book count and pagination support

## Categories Available
Fiction, Non-Fiction, Fantasy, Science Fiction, Mystery, Thriller, Horror, Romance, Historical Fiction, Biography, Self-Help, Business, Science, History, Poetry, Children's Books, Young Adult, Travel, Cookbooks, Philosophy

## Configuration

**Database**: Set `DATABASE_URL` environment variable to use different database (default: SQLite at `./test.db`)

**Static Files**: Served from `/static/` directory

## Known Issues

- Path reference in main.py:20 uses hardcoded "fastapi_demo/static" instead of relative path
- Should be updated to use current directory structure

## Development Notes

- Uses SQLAlchemy for ORM with automatic table creation
- Pydantic models ensure type safety and validation
- Frontend uses vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- CSS uses modern features (Grid, Flexbox, CSS Variables)
- Font Awesome CDN for icons

## Running the Application

1. Install dependencies: `pip install fastapi uvicorn sqlalchemy pydantic`
2. Run server: `uvicorn main:app --reload`
3. Access at `http://localhost:8000`
4. API docs at `http://localhost:8000/docs`

